## Bootstrap a new project

```bash
python scripts/init_project.py \
    --year 2026 --iso3 NLD --short-name journal_trend \
    --display-name "Journal trend analysis" \
    [--session-id 20260318T1620] [--ani-stamp 20260301]
```

This creates the full project scaffold under `projects/<project_id>/` and
writes `.agent-state/active_project.json`.

## Activate an existing project

```bash
python scripts/activate_project.py --project-id 2026_NLD_journal_trend
```

## Session closeout sequence

1. **Closeout:** `python scripts/closeout_project.py --project-id ... --session-id ... --session-status completed`
2. **Lessons (if any):** `python scripts/capture_lessons.py --project-id ... --session-id ... --from-json`
3. **Triage (periodic):** `python scripts/triage_lessons.py`

## Path derivation

All paths derive from `project.yaml`. The manifest is the single source of
truth for local, S3, DBFS, and Databricks workspace paths.

## Anti-patterns

- Do not create projects under `notebooks/` — use `projects/` only
- Do not skip closeout — even partial sessions should produce a summary
- Do not append raw lessons to core-rules.md
- Do not mix project-specific facts with global lessons
